Description: Corroded copper alloy leaf-shaped arrow-head, with a central rib on both sides, edges are rounded near the tip, straight and pointing to the other end forming the tang.
Curator's comments: See parallels London, BM, EA 23916 and GR 1935.0823.114
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1888 / Tanis. Part II. Nebesheh (Am) and Defenneh (Tahpanhes) (p. 77 § 76, pl. xxxix, 11)
Leclère and Spencer 2014 / Tell Dafana Reconsidered: The Archaeology of an Egyptian Frontier Town (p.71, p.183, pl.25)
